{
  "doc_id": "21999",
  "text": "In contrast to these results, Otto [CITATION_1] Corollary 5.3] has shown that a group is automatic with respect to a prefix-closed set of normal forms over a monoid generating set A if and only if there exists a synchronously regular convergent prefix-rewriting system such that for every (u, v) ∈ R, the word v is irreducible over R, and the word u is irreducible over all of the other rewriting rules of R.",
  "correct_citation": {
